ypes of complex inverse\nproblems. In particular, we discuss a bi-dimensional version of the method in\nwhich the photosensor signals integrated over time are used to reconstruct a\ntransverse projection of the event. First results show that, when applied to\ndetector simulation data, the algorithm achieves nearly optimal energy\nresolution (better than 0.5% FWHM at the Q value of $^{136}$Xe) for events\ndistributed over the full active volume of the TPC.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 May 2017 16:01:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-13"}
